displayName: City of Canonas, Magic Academy B1

parameters:
Chef Sitos: A mountain of ingredients... What should I do
with them?

Chef Sitos: Finally some help... Wait, aren't you a
magician!?
Magician Relm: What is it, do you have a problem?

Chef Sitos: Oh no, I never expected you to take care of such
menial tasks.
Magician Relm: I'm not happy about it either, really.
Thief Nora: So, what should I do?

Chef Sitos: I'm sorry to bother you, but could you please
organize the pantry so that it's easier to walk through?
Thief Nora: Understood, leave it to me!
Chef Sitos: Let me know when you're ready!
Chef Sitos: Let me know when you're ready!
Chef Sitos: Alright, let's go! I'll guide you to the pantry!
Chef Sitos: Let me know when you're ready!
Chef Sitos: Alright, let's go! I'll guide you to the pantry!
Thief Nora: W-We finished without any problems!

Chef Sitos: Thank goodness, I was having trouble with the
heavy food supplies.
Chef Sitos: This is the promised reward and gratitude!

Chef Sitos: Since it was from the food storage, keep it a
secret, okay?
Thief Nora: T-Thank you very much!

Chef Sitos: Thanks to you, I've been saved! Ever since I
hurt my back, my work has been getting tougher.

Male Junior Sorcerer: Mealtime is a waste... Wait! If I can
develop a way to simplify meals, I might be able to get
promoted!

Male Junior Sorcerer: While you're daydreaming, I'll make a
name for myself!

Male Junior Sorcerer: Defeating a dragon is certainly a
great achievement! But if you're not creating something,
it's meaningless!

Kanonas Merchant: We transport goods not only from the
Kanonas area, but also from Campus and Myukos.
Dining Hall Lady: Welcome, come and eat your fill!

Cafeteria Lady: Make sure you don't waste any vegetables!
You won't be able to grow up like your friends!

Female Cafeteria Staff: There are so many picky eaters here.
I wonder if their taste buds change because their brain
structure is different?

Female Cafeteria Staff: There are so many picky eaters here.
I wonder if their taste buds change because their brain
structure is different?

Magic Academy Researcher: I eat everything sandwiched in
bread, so I can eat while working!

Female Advanced Magician: I'm from Valier, so sometimes I
get nostalgic for the taste of dusty bread.

Female Advanced Mage: Be careful not to anger the Archmage
too much. She's protecting something... I've never pried
into it though.

Deliveryman: The academy is a large organization, so even
just carrying packages is quite laborious.

Male Deliveryman: I heard it's rare to have a priest at the
academy. I wanted to ask you about a friend of mine.

Male Deliveryman: My friend died on the battlefield... Thank
you for listening and asking about him. I will live on for
his sake too, as he protected me.

Deliveryman: I was troubled by the fact that he died and I
survived, but I'll try my best to live on.

Dining Hall Cook: We have a lot of picky eaters here, and
it's troublesome. Could you help with some special cooking?

Dining Hall Cook: Unfortunately, if I feel like it, I'll let
you know.

Dining Hall Cook: That would be a great help! I'll guide you
to the kitchen!

Dining Hall Cook: Thank you for your help. This is just a
small token of appreciation.

Dining Hall Cook: Oh dear... Well, I guess there's no
helping it.
